chunk_content: When recreating indicators in facilities with an electronic database, and where indicators were calculated by the site using that electronic system, ask the site staff or database manager for the software report or query used to run the calculations, and validate the consistency of that query with partner and/or Ministry of Health definitions for the respective indicator, when possible. Reports are often routine and so definitions and queries used at sites will often be the same across sites using the same electronic systems. 221 ii. A random sample of inactive patient charts (such as 10 charts) should be selected and reviewed to assess misclassification and determine how many may actually still be active. If this review identifies issues with the classification of inactive patient charts, physically counting patient A P charts should be considered (as described in the section on other data validation activities).
